@Shade7x No that's not what I'm saying. They can hapiily make a small niche game if they wish. What I'm saying is they were not trying to make a small niche title! You don't spend that much to only find a small audience. Sony didn't spend 3 billion to get a small niche title. When I mean small audience of course I mean on the scale of Fortnite and Apex. Also if this is such a niche genre how do you explain Arc Raiders numbers?


So what happens if they put in pay to win in Marathon like they did with destiny 2? Do you buy it? I think most would be compelled to. 

I used the stolen art as an example of what scummy things they have done. To be caught 3 times though is disgraceful. I want them to make great games but this isn't it. At the end of the day the numbers are terrible for the amount invested in the game. Yiou can't get away from that. I give it less than 6 months before the layoffs start.

@greebo6799ok. Everyone would like their game to turn out to be a surprise hit. Does this really seem like they spent billions trying to be as broadly popular as possible. It’s a revival of an obscure 30 year old boomer shooter (and again, clearly not going for broad appeal in the visual or gameplay design).
This was likely a relatively low risk project for them, requiring a few maps, and adapting the FPS code they already made for Destiny.
And no, Arc Raiders is not that big. It’s enjoying its moment, but it’s only about 3x more active than Marathon. Not exactly a mega hit either.
